lintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales","Gwynnionith, Deheubarth, Wales":"West Wales, Wales","Cardiganshire,Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Owain","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: shortened form of   O'Callaghan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Callaghan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Dermot, Donal, Kiernan, Niall, Conor, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Siobhan, Tiernan.","Irish (Cork): from Gaelic <b>Ó Ceallacháin</b>, see   Callahan  ."]}]},{"name":"Angharad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Celtic intensive prefix <i>an-</i> + <i>cār</i> ‘love’ + the noun suffix <i>-ad</i>. This was the name of the mother of the 12th-century chronicler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ferch Owain was born in 1250, in Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Owain ap Maredudd, was 21 and her mother, Margred ferch Maelgwn \"Ieunac\", was 51. She had at least 1 son with Owain ap Maredudd. She died in 1320, in Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1250–1320":"1250–1320